
# Week 1 - Cybersecurity Lab Setup

## Goal
Build a cybersecurity home lab to learn Linux, networking, and security tools before starting college.

## Hardware
- Windows 11
- Intel i5 Processor
- 16 GB RAM

## Software Installed
- VirtualBox
- Ubuntu Linux

## Linux Commands Learned

### pwd
Displays the current working directory.

### ls
Lists files and folders.

### mkdir
Creates a directory.

### cd
Changes directories.

### touch
Creates a file.

### cat
Displays file contents.

## Activities Completed
- Installed VirtualBox
- Created Ubuntu virtual machine
- Learned basic Linux commands
- Updated Ubuntu
- Installed Git

## Challenges
I initially had trouble booting Ubuntu because of a VirtualBox graphics issue. I fixed it by changing the display settings and disabling 3D acceleration.

## What I Learned
This week I learned how to create and manage a virtual machine, navigate Linux using the terminal, and organize files using basic Linux commands.

